COVID-19 Status

As of 9:37PM PT mar-28, over 3.4 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 37.5 thousand have died.

In the last day, 5.1 thousand new infections were reported and 37 deaths. Currently 3,911 are in the hospital and 390 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 82.1 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 89.7% have their 1st shot and 85.2% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 13.3 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~541 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.
